name: Shio & hakari
description:
A Kawaii Version of Salt and Light Design
Inspired by: Jennifer S. 

I really didn't know what Kawaii meant, I thought it meant Hawaii style but that was naive of me -.-' It's like, correct me if I'm wrong, all things cute, lovely, and charming. 
I also numbered the figures accordingly for Icebreaker Purposes
(i.e. The Salt has the number 13 because in Matt 5:13 it focuses on salt.) hope

name: Soar
description:
This was actually the anniversary verse for my Home church and the Lord brought me to read it again during a season of mine. I was so blessed that it inspired me to create another design yet I believe this shirt will be more of a sweater. The animal is an eagle as the verse states, and I cornered conveniently the 4 letters of SOAR. I was able to do some letter art with Isaiah and instead of just writing Isaiah 40:31 I used roman numerals, a good conversation starter haha for those who dont know numerals. I also tried using the Salt and Light from the #1 Design and plan on using the lightbulb and saltshaker as the company's mascot. :)
I hope you are encouraged and blessed to Soar!

Isaiah 40:31 (niv)
but those who hope in the LORD will renew their strength. They will soar on wings like eagles; they will run and not grow weary, they will walk and not be faint.

name: Gods Wonders
description:
As soon as i heard this verse I was blessed. I took it to the workshop and designed this summer-esque layout. If you notice I only put the 7 "natural" wonders of the world because i felt that God's purest creations are the ones that are not yet touched by man. I also placed one wonder for each letter of the word "Wonders" which also conveniently contained 7 letters.

The 7 Natural Wonders are:

W - Mount Everest
O - Par√≠cutin volcano
N - Harbor of Rio de Janeiro
D - Great Barrier Reef
E - Victoria Falls
R - Grand Canyon
S - Aurora

Psalms 66:5 (msg)
Take a good look at God's wonders - they'll take your breath away
